    {
      "id": "1433797288278495262",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-10-31T12:38:32.191+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "### Their Own COB Format\n\nGiven the unique requirements of the MOSbius project, the team is designing their own version of a **Chip-on-Board (COB)** package based on the Wafer.Space standard padframe.\n\nTheir application prioritizes **a high number of I/O connections** over power and ground pads, allowing for the maximum number of accessible signals from their transistor array.\n\n**Peter’s student, @xianglin_pui**, has taken the lead on this effort and developed derivative designs that extend the Wafer.Space COB standard for MOSbius’s specialized needs.",
      "author": {
        "id": "756011607603019777",
